---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={`About | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Craig Dennis is a Developer Educator at Cloudflare. He teaches, writes, and creates content to help developers build on the web." />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<article class="about">
				<header class="about-header">
					<h1>About Me</h1>
					<p class="subtitle">Developer Educator, Professional Nerd Clown</p>
				</header>

				<section class="about-content">
					<p>
						Hi there! I'm <strong>Craig Dennis</strong>, and I work as a Developer Educator at 
						<a href="https://cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare</a>. 
						My job is to help developers understand complex technical concepts and build awesome things on the web.
					</p>

					<p>
						The name "Nerd Clown" comes from my daughter. When asked what her dad does for work, 
						she confidently declared that I'm a "nerd clown." And you know what? She nailed it. 
						I spend my days explaining technical concepts in (hopefully) entertaining and accessible ways. 
						I get excited about APIs, edge computing, and making the web better for everyone.
					</p>

					<h2>What I Do</h2>
					<p>
						At Cloudflare, I create tutorials, documentation, videos, and educational content that helps 
						developers get the most out of our platform. Before that, I spent years teaching coding bootcamps 
						and creating educational content for companies like Treehouse.
					</p>
					<p>
						I believe that <em>everyone</em> can learn to code, and that the best way to teach is to 
						meet people where they are. Technical education doesn't have to be dry or intimidating.
					</p>

					<h2>Find Me Online</h2>
					<p>
						I'm <code>@craigsdennis</code> on most platforms. Feel free to reach out, ask questions, 
						or just say hi!
					</p>
					<ul class="social-list">
						<li><a href="https://github.com/craigsdennis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a> - Code, projects, and contributions</li>
						<li><a href="https://twitter.com/craigsdennis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Twitter/X</a> - Quick thoughts and tech takes</li>
						<li><a href="https://bsky.app/profile/craigsdennis.bsky.social" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Bluesky</a> - More quick thoughts</li>
						<li><a href="https://youtube.com/@craigsdennis" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">YouTube</a> - Video tutorials and walkthroughs</li>
					</ul>

					<h2>About This Blog</h2>
					<p>
						This is where I write about things I'm learning, building, and thinking about. 
						Expect posts about web development, Cloudflare Workers, AI/ML, developer tools, 
						and whatever else catches my interest. It's technical, but hopefully fun too.
					</p>
					<p>
						The site is built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Astro</a> 
						and deployed on <a href="https://cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare Pages</a> 
						(naturally).
					</p>
				</section>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.about {
		max-width: 680px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.about-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
		padding-bottom: var(--space-xl);
		border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-color);
	}

	.about-header h1 {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
	}

	.subtitle {
		font-size: 1.125rem;
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.about-content h2 {
		margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
		padding-top: var(--space-lg);
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color);
	}

	.about-content h2:first-of-type {
		border-top: none;
		padding-top: 0;
	}

	.social-list {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-lg) 0;
	}

	.social-list li {
		margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
		padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
		background: var(--bg-surface);
		border-radius: 6px;
		border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
	}

	.social-list a {
		font-weight: 600;
	}
</style>
